<h2><a name="div" id="div">div</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Składnia:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdlib&gt;</span>
    div_t div<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">int</span> x<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="kw4">int</span> y<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span></pre>
<p>

Funkcja div() zwraca iloraz i resztę z dzielenia <em>x</em> przez <em>y</em>. Struktura <em>div_t</em> jest zdefiniowana w pliku <em>cstdlib</em> i zawiera następujące pola:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="kw4">int</span> quot<span class="sy0">;</span>  <span class="co1">//iloraz</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> rem<span class="sy0">;</span>  <span class="co1">//reszta z dzielenia</span></pre>
<p>

Dla przykładu, poniższy kod:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="kw4">int</span> x <span class="sy0">=</span> <span class="nu0">8</span><span class="sy0">;</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> y <span class="sy0">=</span> <span class="nu0">3</span><span class="sy0">;</span>
    div_t z <span class="sy0">=</span> div<span class="br0">&#40;</span>x<span class="sy0">,</span> y<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span>
&nbsp;
    <a href="http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/printf.html"><span class="kw3">printf</span></a><span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="st0">&quot;%d / %d = %d i reszta %d<span class="es1">\n</span>&quot;</span><span class="sy0">,</span> x<span class="sy0">,</span> y<span class="sy0">,</span> z.<span class="me1">quot</span><span class="sy0">,</span> z.<span class="me1">rem</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span></pre>
<p>

spowoduje wyświetlenie:
</p>
<pre class="code">
    8 / 3 = 2 i reszta 2</pre>
<p>
C++ dostarcza przeciążoną wersję funkcji:

</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdlib&gt;</span>
    ldiv_t div<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">long</span> x<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="kw4">long</span> y<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span>  <span class="co1">//to samo co ldiv()</span></pre>
<p>
Tematy pokrewne: <a href="ldiv" class="wikilink1" title="pl:c:math:ldiv">ldiv</a>
</p>

</div>
